{"type":"message","id":"1df1c165","parentId":"eff11290","timestamp":"2026-04-08T07:20:35.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the simulated paper portfolio for 2026-04-08. Let me now summarize what I found:\n\n**Simulated Paper Portfolio Holdings (latest/2026-04-08):** 10 stocks\n1. 002025.SZ - 3600股, 成本 60.1248\n2. 002173.SZ - 4100股, 成本 29.6262\n3. 002342.SZ - 7700股, 成本 14.4127\n4. 002471.SZ - 17500股, 成本 9.1833\n\n\n5. 300129.SZ - 19700股, 成本 15.1532\n6. 300342.SZ - 400股, 成本 46.9816\n7. 300503.SZ - 2100股, 成本 52.076\n8. 301018.SZ - 2800股, 成本 102.5807\n9. 603626.SH - 6400股, 成本 23.3206\n10. 603778.SH - 6800股, 成本 22.0195\n\nNow I'm looking at today's trading activity, starting with the sell orders that were executed.\n\nThe stop-loss sell signals are hitting for four positions: 002173.SZ with a -19.09% loss, 002342.SZ at -10.63%, 300129.SZ down -21.73%, and 301018.SZ falling -13.91%. Meanwhile, new buy signals are coming in for 002218.SZ, 002222.SZ, 002467.SZ, and 002792.SZ.\n\nLooking at the trading journal entries from today, there's a buy execution for 002179.SZ at 35.49 for 1900 shares, though I'm noticing the execution holdings file shows a different set of 10 stocks that don't seem to match what I'm seeing in the signals or journal entries.\n\nAfter cross-referencing the stop-loss targets with the current holdings, I can see which positions are being cut: 002173, 002342, 300129, and 301018 are all marked for exit, while 002025, 300342, 603626, and 603778 remain in the portfolio. So I need to sell these four positions and roll the proceeds into the new buy signals.\n\nLooking at the new buy candidates, the stop-loss is creating meaningful turnover—the portfolio will lose about 53% of its current positions and replace them with fresh entries. This is a significant shift that I should flag in the daily report since it's substantially different from the previous day's holdings.","thinkingSignature"