{"type":"message","id":"1b8fc4fb","parentId":"069d8f08","timestamp":"2026-04-08T07:20:57.595Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a very clear picture of the situation:\n\n**Today's signals (2026-04-08):**\n\n**SELL (4 stop-loss exits):**\n1. 002173.XSHE - 4100股, 亏 -19.09%\n2. 002342.XSHE - 7700股, 亏 -10.63%\n3. 300129.XSHE - 19700股, 亏 -21.73%\n4. 301018.XSHE - 2800股, 亏 -13.91%\n\n\n5. \nFor the buys, only two orders went through—002222.XSHE and 301550.XSHE—while six others were blocked due to hitting the daily buying limit. The four exit positions will free up roughly 678,363元 in capital from the paper portfolio.\n\nAfter the sells, the remaining six holdings are 002025, 300342, 603626, and 603778 with a combined cost basis around 1,026,000元, though the stop-loss executions would reduce this significantly. The real issue is that I'm working with incomplete data—the paper portfolio reports only capture signals through 2026-03-30, and I don't have today's actual execution results. The approved signals show the stop-losses were triggered today, but the execution holdings file appears to be from an earlier date, so I'm missing the actual fills.\n\nI should pull today's execution report and notify the user that the simulation has shifted to these new positions, then verify the signals in the system match what I'm seeing.","thinkingSignature":"6390e1887f27ea2d9bf672f6f3d91015fb4cb89f9a0bb4a41458f40f0fbed23f"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！找到了。`personal-a-share-research-system` 今天有完整数据。现在清楚了：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_55fyih9bj6xp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_aggressive_exit_holdings_20260408.csv 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22356,"output":406,"cacheRead":20037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42799,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,